Mimosa pudica

   [1478.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms
   Common names sensitive plant, humble plant, shame plant, touch-me-not
   tree, live-and-die, acacia pudica, sensitiva, malicia de mulher,
   juqueri rasteiro, tuitui, cogadrogadro, lajwania
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 1478

   Notes
   GROWING PERIOD
   Annual or perennial herb. It flowers throughout the year and can
   complete its life cycle in 90 days.
   COMMON NAMES
   Sensitive plant, Sien-sien, Hila hila, Sensitive, Putri mula, Bujang
   kaget, Kucingan, Memalu, Malu-malu, Makahiya, Torog-torog, Babain, Smau
   banla, Bankrap, F'a:z langab, Th'ub nhub, Maiyarep, Ya-ngap, Xau ho,
   Trinh nu.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: M. pudica var. tetrandra, M. tetrandra, M.
   tetranda var. unijuga, M. unijuga, M. hirsuta, M. pudibunda. Sensitive
   plant probably originated in South America. It is well adapted to humid
   areas with high winds. In dryland field crops, in rainfed wetland rice
   and in plantation crops it can become a noixious weed. When the
   prickles on the stem and the fruits become to hard, they can cause
   intestinal inflamation in animals.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Mannetje L 1992 pp 167-169 [USE, FER, DRA, LIG, TEXT, PH]
   Skerman P 1988 pp 352-353 [RAIN, LIMIT]

